						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jāṭāvarman</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tribhº Vīrapāṇḍyadēva I: Year 6 = 1258-59 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged in some places.</p>						

						<p>It records that the <hi rend="italic">śrībhaṇḍārāttār</hi> (authorities) of the temple of the god Uttamaśōḻaviṉṉagar-emperumāṉ received (Uttamaśōḻapuram) of money from a certain Tiruveḻundūr Nārāyaṇaṉ Nārāyaṇa-bhaṭṭaṉ of Uttamaśōḻach-chaturvvēdimaṅgalam and gave the same to the stone mason for providing the pavement caused to be done in the Śēranāryaṇaṉ-maṇḍapa, by a certain Uḍaiyār Kaḷappālar. </p>						

						</summary>
